[1
Date: Sun, 08 Feb 1998 13:21:47 -0300
From: Luiz Jacintho da Silva <luisjs@guttenberg.correionet.com.br>

There must be some degree of misinformation. Even if used in higher
concentrations, and injected subcutaneously, BCG vaccine will not cause
tuberculosis. Disseminated BCG infection, that keeps certain similarity
with tuberculosis may occur, but it can be differentiated in clinical,
epidemiological and microbiological grounds.
Errors bound to happen if untrained personnel are employed are:
(1) inadequate dilution, i.e., a higher than appropriate concentration is
injected
(2) injection of larger volumes
(3) subcutaneous injection.
--
Luiz Jacintho da Silva. M.D.
