From: Robert Rakita <rakita@heart.med.uth.tmc.edu>

I'm sorry to be so obtuse, but could one of the moderators, or perhaps the
originator of this report, explain to me how tuberculosis can be acquired
by vaccination? I am only guessing that the vaccination being discussed is
the use of BCG - is this correct? As far as I knew, this could not result
in transmission of active tuberculosis, though immunosuppressed patients
can develop disseminated disease with BCG.
