[4
Date: Tue, 10 Feb 1998 09:40:40 -0500
From: Barbara Robinson-Dunn <Robinson-DunnB@state.mi.us>

I am concerned about the content of this report. It implies that a group of
children were vaccinated with BCG (?) and came down with tuberculosis. A
number of questions must be answered. Was the vaccine actually BCG? Was it
contaminated with a virulent form of _M. bovis_ or _M. tuberculosis_? Was
the difficulty in treating these children due to the presence of drug
resistant organisms? How did the disease present? Could you please request
additional information about this very disturbing issue?
--
Dr. Barbara Robinson-Dunn
Director of Microbiology
Michigan Department of Community Health
e-mail: Robinson-DunnB@state.mi.us
[With varying degrees of collegiality subscribers have pointed out that
complications associated with BCG vaccination are uncommon when the vaccine
is used properly, and that when they do occur, those complications are
distinguishible from classical presentations of tuberculosis. It should be
noted that post-vaccination complications in children have been reported to
include lymphadenitis (1-4) and osteitis (1,4), and a syndrome referred to
as multisystem postvaccination tuberculosis (3). It is apparent from the
literature that there are several strains of BCG vaccine organism in use
around the globe, and that the Moscow BCG strain has previously been known
to cause complications in a dose-dependent manner. We cannot tell from the
previous posting which vaccine strain was used, or the precise nature of
the complications observed. Additional information from those familiar with
the outbreak would be appreciated. Thanks to all who responded. - Mod.ES
References:
1. Vitkova, E. et al. Adverse Reactions to BCG. Cent. Eur. J. Public
Health 3:138-141, 1995.
2. Hengster, P. et al. Occurance of suppurative lymphadenitis after a
change of BCG vaccine. Arch. Dis. Child., 67:952-5, 1992.
3. Karnak, I, et al. Is BCG vaccine innocent? Pediatr. Surg. Int.
12:220-223, 1997.
4. Marik, I., et al. Osteitis caused by BCG vaccination. J. Pediatr.
Orthop. 8: 333-337, 1988.
